{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_018ViEY1Wa9LSvtAekoE9m6s","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01YBEZeKr6rp5QRXQ6MApSvb","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection.md","content":"# Story 8.3: cargo-tarpaulin coverage detection and parsing\n\nStatus: ready-for-dev\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer running coverage on a Rust project,\nI want codeharness to detect cargo-tarpaulin, run it, and parse the JSON report,\nso that coverage metrics are tracked at parity with Node.js/Python.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. Given a Rust project with `cargo-tarpaulin` installed, when `detectCoverageTool()` is called, then it returns `{ tool: 'cargo-tarpaulin', runCommand: 'cargo tarpaulin --out json --output-dir coverage/', reportFormat: 'tarpaulin-json' }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n2. Given a Rust workspace project (Cargo.toml contains `[workspace]`), when `detectCoverageTool()` is called, then the run command includes `--workspace` flag <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n3. Given a `coverage/tarpaulin-report.json` file with `\"coverage\": 85.5`, when `parseCoverageReport()` is called with format `'tarpaulin-json'`, then it returns `85.5` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n4. Given `cargo test` output containing `test result: ok. 42 passed; 3 failed; 0 ignored`, when `parseTestCounts()` is called, then it returns `{ passCount: 42, failCount: 3 }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n5. Given `cargo-tarpaulin` is NOT installed, when `detectCoverageTool()` is called on a Rust project, then it returns `{ tool: 'unknown' }` with a warning <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [ ] Task 1: Update `detectCoverageTool()` rust branch (AC: #1, #2, #5)\n  - [ ] 1.1 Add `cargo-tarpaulin` installation check via `cargo tarpaulin --version` subprocess\n  - [ ] 1.2 Return `{ tool: 'unknown' }` with warning if not installed\n  - [ ] 1.3 Update `runCommand` to `'cargo tarpaulin --out json --output-dir coverage/'`\n  - [ ] 1.4 Add workspace detection: read Cargo.toml, check for `[workspace]`, append `--workspace` if present\n- [ ] Task 2: Add `tarpaulin-json` branch to `parseCoverageReport()` (AC: #3)\n  - [ ] 2.1 Create `parseTarpaulinCoverage()` function\n  - [ ] 2.2 Read `coverage/tarpaulin-report.json`, extract top-level `\"coverage\"` field\n  - [ ] 2.3 Wire into `parseCoverageReport()` switch\n- [ ] Task 3: Add `cargo test` output parsing to `parseTestCounts()` (AC: #4)\n  - [ ] 3.1 Add regex for `test result: ok. N passed; N failed; N ignored` format\n  - [ ] 3.2 Handle both ok and FAILED result lines\n- [ ] Task 4: Write unit tests for all new code paths\n  - [ ] 4.1 Tests for detectCoverageTool rust with tarpaulin installed/not installed\n  - [ ] 4.2 Tests for workspace flag inclusion\n  - [ ] 4.3 Tests for parseTarpaulinCoverage with valid/invalid/missing report\n  - [ ] 4.4 Tests for parseTestCounts with cargo test output format\n  - [ ] 4.5 Tests for cargo test output with failures\n- [ ] Task 5: Run full test suite — zero regressions\n\n## Dev Notes\n\n### Current State of Rust Coverage Code\n\nStory 8-2 already added the rust branch to `detectCoverageTool()` in `src/lib/coverage.ts` (line 51-57). However, it is incomplete:\n\n1. **No tarpaulin install check** — current code unconditionally returns `cargo-tarpaulin` for any rust project. AC #5 requires checking if tarpaulin is actually installed and returning `unknown` if not.\n2. **Wrong runCommand** — current returns `'cargo tarpaulin --out json'` but AC #1 specifies `'cargo tarpaulin --out json --output-dir coverage/'` (output-dir ensures report lands in standard location).\n3. **No workspace detection** — AC #2 requires `--workspace` flag for workspace projects.\n4. **No tarpaulin report parsing** — `parseCoverageReport()` has no `tarpaulin-json` branch. It currently falls through to `return 0`.\n5. **No cargo test output parsing** — `parseTestCounts()` handles vitest, jest, and pytest formats but NOT `cargo test` format.\n\n### Implementation Approach\n\n**File: `src/lib/coverage.ts`** — All changes go here. This is the single file that needs modification.\n\n#### detectCoverageTool rust branch (replace lines 51-57)\n\n```typescript\nif (stack === 'rust') {\n  // Check if cargo-tarpaulin is installed\n  try {\n    execSync('cargo tarpaulin --version', { stdio: 'pipe', timeout: 10_000 });\n  } catch {\n    warn('cargo-tarpaulin not installed — coverage detection unavailable');\n    return { tool: 'unknown', runCommand: '', reportFormat: '' };\n  }\n\n  // Detect workspace: read Cargo.toml for [workspace] section\n  const cargoPath = join(baseDir, 'Cargo.toml');\n  let isWorkspace = false;\n  try {\n    const cargoContent = readFileSync(cargoPath, 'utf-8');\n    isWorkspace = /^\\[workspace\\]/m.test(cargoContent);\n  } catch { /* no Cargo.toml — not a workspace */ }\n\n  const wsFlag = isWorkspace ? ' --workspace' : '';\n  return {\n    tool: 'cargo-tarpaulin',\n    runCommand: `cargo tarpaulin --out json --output-dir coverage/${wsFlag}`,\n    reportFormat: 'tarpaulin-json',\n  };\n}\n```\n\n#### parseCoverageReport — add tarpaulin-json branch\n\nAdd before the `return 0` fallthrough:\n\n```typescript\nif (format === 'tarpaulin-json') {\n  return parseTarpaulinCoverage(dir);\n}\n```\n\nNew function:\n\n```typescript\nfunction parseTarpaulinCoverage(dir: string): number {\n  const reportPath = join(dir, 'coverage', 'tarpaulin-report.json');\n  if (!existsSync(reportPath)) {\n    warn('Tarpaulin coverage report not found at coverage/tarpaulin-report.json');\n    return 0;\n  }\n  try {\n    const report = JSON.parse(readFileSync(reportPath, 'utf-8')) as { coverage?: number };\n    return report.coverage ?? 0;\n  } catch {\n    warn('Failed to parse tarpaulin coverage report');\n    return 0;\n  }\n}\n```\n\n#### parseTestCounts — add cargo test format\n\nAdd before the final `return { passCount: 0, failCount: 0 }`:\n\n```typescript\n// cargo test format: \"test result: ok. 42 passed; 3 failed; 0 ignored\"\nconst cargoMatch = /test result:.*?(\\d+)\\s+passed;\\s*(\\d+)\\s+failed/i.exec(output);\nif (cargoMatch) {\n  return {\n    passCount: parseInt(cargoMatch[1], 10),\n    failCount: parseInt(cargoMatch[2], 10),\n  };\n}\n```\n\n### Architecture Constraints\n\n- **<300 line file limit**: `coverage.ts` is currently 568 lines. Adding ~40 lines keeps it under safe limits for a single file but consider that it's already over 300. If refactoring is needed, extract rust-specific functions. However, since the existing file already exceeds 300 lines, follow the existing pattern rather than splitting.\n- **Result<T> pattern**: `detectCoverageTool` returns `CoverageToolInfo`, not `Result<T>`. Follow existing convention.\n- **No new npm dependencies**: All parsing uses built-in `JSON.parse` and regex. `execSync` already imported.\n- **NFR4**: Cargo.toml parsing uses simple regex matching — no TOML parser dependency. Same pattern as `stack-detect.ts`.\n\n### Tarpaulin Report Format\n\nThe `tarpaulin-report.json` has this top-level structure:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"coverage\": 85.5,\n  \"files\": [ ... ]\n}\n```\n\nThe `coverage` field is the overall percentage (0-100 float). This is the only field we need to parse.\n\n### Cargo Test Output Format\n\nStandard cargo test output format:\n\n```\ntest result: ok. 42 passed; 3 failed; 0 ignored; 0 measured; 0 filtered out; finished in 1.23s\n```\n\nOr on failure:\n\n```\ntest result: FAILED. 10 passed; 2 failed; 0 ignored; 0 measured; 0 filtered out; finished in 0.50s\n```\n\nThe regex `test result:.*?(\\d+)\\s+passed;\\s*(\\d+)\\s+failed` captures both formats.\n\n### Testing Patterns\n\nFollow `src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts` existing patterns:\n- Use `mkdtempSync` for temp directories\n- Write fixture files (Cargo.toml, tarpaulin-report.json) to temp dir\n- Mock `execSync` for tarpaulin install check using `vi.mock` or `vi.spyOn`\n- Clean up in `afterEach`\n\n### Project Structure Notes\n\n- All changes in `src/lib/coverage.ts` and `src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts`\n- No new files needed\n- No module boundary changes\n- Follows existing `detectCoverageTool` → `parseCoverageReport` → `parseTestCounts` pipeline\n\n### References\n\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-rust-stack-support.md#Epic 2: Rust Coverage & Testing]\n- [Source: src/lib/coverage.ts — detectCoverageTool, parseCoverageReport, parseTestCounts]\n- [Source: src/lib/stack-detect.ts — detectStack, workspace pattern from getCargoDepsSection]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust.md — previous story learnings]\n- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/architecture-operational-excellence.md — <300 line limit, Result<T> pattern]\n\n### Previous Story Intelligence (8-2)\n\nKey learnings from story 8-2:\n- The `detectCoverageTool()` rust branch was added in 8-2's code review fix, returning hardcoded `cargo-tarpaulin` without install check. This story must replace that stub with the full implementation.\n- `getStackLabel()` and `generateAgentsMdContent()` already handle rust (added in 8-2 review fixes). Do NOT duplicate.\n- `getDefaultState()` now returns `cargo-tarpaulin` for rust stack (added in 8-2 review). Do NOT duplicate.\n- The `CoverageToolInfo.tool` type union already includes `'cargo-tarpaulin'`. No type changes needed.\n- Test suite was at 2968 tests after 8-2. Zero regressions expected.\n\n### Git Intelligence\n\nRecent commits (d6a76bf, 9ddd65e, 4c7f498) show:\n- Story 8-2 modified: `state.ts`, `coverage.ts`, `stack-detect.ts`, `docs-scaffold.ts` + their tests\n- The rust branch in `detectCoverageTool` (coverage.ts:51-57) was added as a code review fix in 8-2\n- Cargo.toml parsing patterns already established in `stack-detect.ts` (getCargoDepsSection, hasCargoDep)\n\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n## Verification Requirements\n\n- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection.proof.md`)\n- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n\n## Documentation Requirements\n\n- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection.md`\n\n## Testing Requirements\n\n- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n\n## Dev Agent Record\n\n### Agent Model Used\n\n### Debug Log References\n\n### Completion Notes List\n\n### File List\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":424,"cache_read_input_tokens":47747,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":424,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01L8FFCpVh7KBCcfMN3fKhC4","session_id":"900ad046-8ed4-4678-b2b2-9fd66fbde286","uuid":"c7de20f9-43fa-4710-9070-d3a9b857eb44"}
