{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AgMkvmueaRUBzKkNvM32t8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 8-3: cargo-tarpaulin Coverage Detection and Parsing\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer running coverage on a Rust project,\n     8→I want codeharness to detect cargo-tarpaulin, run it, and parse the JSON report,\n     9→So that coverage metrics are tracked at parity with Node.js/Python.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given a Rust project with `cargo-tarpaulin` installed, when `detectCoverageTool()` is called, then it returns `{ tool: 'cargo-tarpaulin', runCommand: 'cargo tarpaulin --out json --output-dir coverage/', reportFormat: 'tarpaulin-json' }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given a Rust workspace project, when `detectCoverageTool()` is called, then the run command includes `--workspace` flag <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC3: Given a `coverage/tarpaulin-report.json` file with `\"coverage\": 85.5`, when `parseCoverageReport()` is called with format `'tarpaulin-json'`, then it returns `85.5` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [ ] AC4: Given `cargo test` output containing `test result: ok. 42 passed; 3 failed; 0 ignored`, when `parseTestCounts()` is called, then it returns `{ passCount: 42, failCount: 3 }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→- [ ] AC5: Given `cargo-tarpaulin` is NOT installed, when `detectCoverageTool()` is called on a Rust project, then it returns `{ tool: 'unknown' }` with a warning <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→\n    19→## Technical Notes\n    20→\n    21→### Coverage Tool Detection\n    22→\n    23→File: `src/lib/coverage.ts` — `detectCoverageTool()` at L35-53.\n    24→\n    25→Add `if (stack === 'rust') { return detectRustCoverageTool(baseDir); }` at L47 (after existing stack checks).\n    26→\n    27→Create `detectRustCoverageTool(baseDir: string)` function:\n    28→1. Check `Cargo.toml` exists (sanity check)\n    29→2. Check if `cargo-tarpaulin` is installed: try `cargo tarpaulin --version` via `execFileSync`\n    30→3. If installed, return `{ tool: 'cargo-tarpaulin', runCommand: 'cargo tarpaulin --out json --output-dir coverage/', reportFormat: 'tarpaulin-json' }`\n    31→4. For workspace projects (detect `[workspace]` in `Cargo.toml`), add `--workspace` flag to `runCommand`\n    32→5. If not installed, return `{ tool: 'unknown' }` with a warning log\n    33→\n    34→### Coverage Report Parsing\n    35→\n    36→File: `src/lib/coverage.ts` — `parseCoverageReport()` at L257.\n    37→\n    38→Add `'tarpaulin-json'` case. Create `parseTarpaulinCoverage(reportDir: string)` function:\n    39→1. Read `coverage/tarpaulin-report.json`\n    40→2. Parse JSON\n    41→3. Extract top-level `coverage` field (float 0-100)\n    42→4. Return the number directly\n    43→\n    44→Tarpaulin JSON format: `{ \"files\": [...], \"coverage\": 85.5 }` — the top-level `coverage` field is the overall percentage.\n    45→\n    46→### Test Output Parsing\n    47→\n    48→File: `src/lib/coverage.ts` — `parseTestCounts()` at L308.\n    49→\n    50→Add regex for `cargo test` output format:\n    51→```typescript\n    52→/test result: ok\\. (\\d+) passed; (\\d+) failed/\n    53→```\n    54→\n    55→This matches: `test result: ok. 42 passed; 3 failed; 0 ignored`\n    56→\n    57→### Type Changes\n    58→\n    59→`CoverageToolInfo.tool` type union must include `'cargo-tarpaulin'` (see story 8-2). `reportFormat` must accept `'tarpaulin-json'`.\n    60→\n    61→### Tests\n    62→\n    63→File: `src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts`\n    64→\n    65→Mirror existing Node.js/Python test patterns. Use `vi.mock('node:fs')` and `vi.mock('node:child_process')`. Test cases:\n    66→- Tarpaulin installed → returns correct CoverageToolInfo\n    67→- Tarpaulin not installed → returns `{ tool: 'unknown' }`\n    68→- Workspace project → `--workspace` flag in runCommand\n    69→- Tarpaulin JSON parsing → extracts `coverage` field\n    70→- `cargo test` output parsing → correct pass/fail counts\n    71→- Missing report file → graceful error\n    72→\n    73→## Files to Change\n    74→\n    75→- `src/lib/coverage.ts` — Add `detectRustCoverageTool()` function, add `parseTarpaulinCoverage()` function, add `'tarpaulin-json'` case to `parseCoverageReport()` (L257), add cargo test regex to `parseTestCounts()` (L308), add Rust branch to `detectCoverageTool()` (L47)\n    76→- `src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts` — Add Rust coverage test cases for detection, parsing, workspace flag, and test output parsing\n    77→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01L8FFCpVh7KBCcfMN3fKhC4","session_id":"900ad046-8ed4-4678-b2b2-9fd66fbde286","uuid":"7725385f-264d-4b28-94eb-0c21f728e10c","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:53:47.976Z"}
