{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01L8FFCpVh7KBCcfMN3fKhC4","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Story file created at `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection.md`.\n\n**Story Details:**\n- **Story ID:** 8.3\n- **Story Key:** 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection\n- **File:** `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection.md`\n- **Status:** ready-for-dev\n- **Sprint status file:** NOT modified (per instructions)\n\n**What the story covers:**\n- 5 ACs covering: tarpaulin detection with install check, workspace flag, tarpaulin JSON report parsing, cargo test output parsing, graceful fallback when tarpaulin is missing\n- All 5 ACs tagged `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` — each can be verified by calling the relevant function in a unit test subprocess\n- Single file change: `src/lib/coverage.ts` (+ tests in `src/lib/__tests__/coverage.test.ts`)\n- Replaces the stub rust branch added in story 8-2's code review fix with the full implementation\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Problems encountered:**\n- The story file already existed with a partial/draft version (status: backlog). Overwrote it with the complete version.\n\n**Workarounds applied:**\n- None.\n\n**Risks identified:**\n- `coverage.ts` is already 568 lines (exceeds the architecture's 300-line limit). This story adds ~40 more lines. The pre-existing violation means the dev agent may feel pressure to refactor, but the story explicitly says to follow existing pattern and not split the file.\n- AC #5 (tarpaulin not installed check) requires `execSync('cargo tarpaulin --version')` which adds a subprocess call to what was previously a pure filesystem check. Tests will need to mock `execSync`, which the existing test file doesn't do for rust — could be tricky depending on how mocks are structured.\n\n**Observations:**\n- All 5 ACs are genuinely CLI-verifiable via unit tests — no integration-required tags needed. Each AC exercises a pure function or a function with a mockable subprocess call.\n- Story 8-2's code review already added a minimal rust branch to `detectCoverageTool` — this story replaces that stub. The \"Do NOT Duplicate\" section in the story explicitly lists what 8-2 already handled to prevent the dev agent from re-implementing those pieces."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ad13197e2fa5f843c (use SendMessage with to: 'ad13197e2fa5f843c' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 57632\ntool_uses: 28\nduration_ms: 222814</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"900ad046-8ed4-4678-b2b2-9fd66fbde286","uuid":"ef1d3372-d23a-4f39-a879-71f3b4cc1bfb","timestamp":"2026-03-23T05:54:54.459Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /create-story for story 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection. The sprint-status.yaml is at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/sprint-status.yaml. Auto-discover the next backlog story and create it. For each AC, append `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` or `<!-- verification: integration-required -->` based on whether the AC can be verified by running CLI commands in a subprocess. ACs referencing workflows, sprint planning, user sessions, or external system interactions should be tagged as integration-required. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Problems encountered (errors, ambiguities in epic definition, missing context)\n- Workarounds applied (anything you did that felt hacky or suboptimal)\n- Risks identified (ACs that seem untestable, unclear requirements, missing dependencies)\n- Observations (anything surprising or noteworthy about this story)\nIf nothing to report, write `## Session Issues\\n\\nNone.`","agentId":"ad13197e2fa5f843c","content":[{"type":"text","text"