{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01UAKaXeCTGPBzDiK6oMZVXi","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_017azDsvkohm6bPBWjEMWq6k","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","old_string":"- **Mock complexity:** AC #5 (tarpaulin not installed) requires `execSync` mock for rust path — existing tests don't mock `execSync` for rust yet.","new_string":"- **Mock complexity:** AC #5 (tarpaulin not installed) requires `execSync` mock for rust path — existing tests don't mock `execSync` for rust yet.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — dev-story (2026-03-23T06:02Z)\n\n- **ESM mocking limitation:** `vi.spyOn` cannot spy on `execSync` from `node:child_process` in ESM mode. Used `vi.mock('node:child_process', async (importOriginal) => ...)` as workaround — adds file-level mock applying to all tests (mitigated by `mockReset()` in `afterEach`).\n- **Cargo test regex ordering:** The cargo test regex was placed before pytest regex because pytest regex would false-match on cargo test output. Ordering matters — fragile to reordering by future contributors.\n- **No integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` execution:** All tests mock the subprocess call. Consistent with existing Node.js/Python coverage tool tests in codebase."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":798,"cache_read_input_tokens":41858,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":798},"output_tokens":65,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"900ad046-8ed4-4678-b2b2-9fd66fbde286","uuid":"37d76f8e-8b4e-45d7-93a9-5cb5c18d8127"}
