{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017azDsvkohm6bPBWjEMWq6k","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"900ad046-8ed4-4678-b2b2-9fd66fbde286","uuid":"2ae7fe91-ee2d-4d0a-b553-06cc301783a5","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:01:26.832Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"- **Mock complexity:** AC #5 (tarpaulin not installed) requires `execSync` mock for rust path — existing tests don't mock `execSync` for rust yet.","newString":"- **Mock complexity:** AC #5 (tarpaulin not installed) requires `execSync` mock for rust path — existing tests don't mock `execSync` for rust yet.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — dev-story (2026-03-23T06:02Z)\n\n- **ESM mocking limitation:** `vi.spyOn` cannot spy on `execSync` from `node:child_process` in ESM mode. Used `vi.mock('node:child_process', async (importOriginal) => ...)` as workaround — adds file-level mock applying to all tests (mitigated by `mockReset()` in `afterEach`).\n- **Cargo test regex ordering:** The cargo test regex was placed before pytest regex because pytest regex would false-match on cargo test output. Ordering matters — fragile to reordering by future contributors.\n- **No integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` execution:** All tests mock the subprocess call. Consistent with existing Node.js/Python coverage tool tests in codebase.","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-23\n\n### 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust — verify (2026-03-23T05:45Z)\n\n- **Leftover container:** Previous session left `codeharness-verify` container running. Had to clean up before starting fresh verification.\n- **Stack detection mismatch:** `codeharness status --check-docker` reported stack as down, but shared stack containers were running (using `codeharness-shared-*` naming). The `docker-compose.harness.yml` tried to start duplicate containers and hit port conflicts. Worked around by using the shared stack directly.\n- **Observability gap:** Both AC1 and AC2 verifications showed no log events emitted to VictoriaLogs during `codeharness init` operations. Silent code path.\n- **Beads sync failure:** `codeharness sync` couldn't find story Status line in the story file — likely looking for `## Status:` pattern that was stripped or mismatched.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — create-story (2026-03-23T05:55Z)\n\n- **Pre-existing file:** Story file already existed with partial/draft version (status: backlog). Overwrote with complete version.\n- **File size risk:** `coverage.ts` is already 568 lines (exceeds 300-line architecture limit). Story adds ~40 more lines. Explicitly noted not to refactor/split.\n- **Mock complexity:** AC #5 (tarpaulin not installed) requires `execSync` mock for rust path — existing tests don't mock `execSync` for rust yet.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":12,"oldLines":3,"newStart":12,"newLines":9,"lines":[" - **Pre-existing file:** Story file already existed with partial/draft version (status: backlog). Overwrote with complete version."," - **File size risk:** `coverage.ts` is already 568 lines (exceeds 300-line architecture limit). Story adds ~40 more lines. Explicitly noted not to refactor/split."," - **Mock complexity:** AC #5 (tarpaulin not installed) requires `execSync` mock for rust path — existing tests don't mock `execSync` for rust yet.","+","+### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — dev-story (2026-03-23T06:02Z)","+","+- **ESM mocking limitation:** `vi.spyOn` cannot spy on `execSync` from `node:child_process` in ESM mode. Used `vi.mock('node:child_process', async (importOriginal) => ...)` as workaround — adds file-level mock applying to all tests (mitigated by `mockReset()` in `afterEach`).","+- **Cargo test regex ordering:** The cargo test regex was placed before pytest regex because pytest regex would false-match on cargo test output. Ordering matters — fragile to reordering by future contributors.","+- **No integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` execution:** All tests mock the subprocess call. Consistent with existing Node.js/Python coverage tool tests in codebase."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
