{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01PvBQn2mNZRS7GvSEiRGpp5","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Ga1BEUjDLezv6GzGbUN5QD","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","old_string":"- **No integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` execution:** All tests mock the subprocess call. Consistent with existing Node.js/Python coverage tool tests in codebase.","new_string":"- **No integration test for actual `cargo tarpaulin` execution:** All tests mock the subprocess call. Consistent with existing Node.js/Python coverage tool tests in codebase.\n\n### 8-3-cargo-tarpaulin-coverage-detection — code-review (2026-03-23T06:07Z)\n\n- **HIGH bug fixed:** `parseTestCounts()` only captured first `test result:` line from cargo test output. Workspace projects emit one per crate, so counts were wrong. Fixed with global regex + aggregation loop.\n- **LOW not fixed:** No type validation on `parseTarpaulinCoverage` — if tarpaulin outputs `\"coverage\": \"85.5\"` (string), `?? 0` won't catch it. Low risk.\n- **LOW not fixed:** `checkOnlyCoverage()` shells out to `cargo tarpaulin --version` for Rust projects — unnecessary side effect in check-only mode. Pre-existing pattern.\n- **Coverage note:** `coverage.ts` branch coverage 77.98% (below 80% floor for branches) — caused by pre-existing untested branches, not new Rust code. Statement coverage 90.51% passes.\n- **Time constraint:** Verification not started — insufficient time remaining in session budget. Story left at `verifying` for next session."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1064,"cache_read_input_tokens":45142,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1064},"output_tokens":72,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"900ad046-8ed4-4678-b2b2-9fd66fbde286","uuid":"71eca4e3-26cd-47ab-bd31-830a33238915"}
