{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BtWX3hQY2oEX7GcMZV9tEY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-23\n     2→\n     3→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence Sprint\n     4→**Session window:** ~09:08 - 09:46 UTC+4 (~38 minutes)\n     5→**Ralph iterations:** 2 (iteration 1 timed out at 30 minutes)\n     6→**Commits produced:** 3\n     7→\n     8→---\n     9→\n    10→## 1. Session Summary\n    11→\n    12→| Story | Outcome | Commits | Notes |\n    13→|-------|---------|---------|-------|\n    14→| 8-1-rust-stack-and-app-type-detection | done | `4c7f498` | Rust stack detection, app type inference from Cargo.toml |\n    15→| 8-2-expand-state-types-for-rust | done (in sprint-status.yaml), verifying (in state-snapshot) | `9ddd65e`, `d6a76bf` | Needed a fix commit for AC2 (rust_env_hint in OTLP state) |\n    16→\n    17→Two stories attempted, two completed. Epic 8.1 (Rust Detection Foundation) is complete. Ralph timed out on iteration 1 after 30 minutes — it completed 8-1 impl+verify plus 8-2 impl+verify but was mid-retrospective when the timer expired. Iteration 2 picked up and produced the verification commit for 8-2.\n    18→\n    19→---\n    20→\n    21→## 2. Issues Analysis\n    22→\n    23→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation\n    24→\n    25→| Severity | Story | Issue | Fixed? |\n    26→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n    27→| HIGH | 8-1 | `[dev-dependencies]`/`[build-dependencies]` deps incorrectly matched as production deps — false positive server/agent detection | Yes — added `getCargoDepsSection()` |\n    28→| HIGH | 8-1 | Substring false positives on crate names (`anthropic` matching `anthropic-sdk`, `rocket` matching `sprocket`) | Yes — added `hasCargoDep()` with word-boundary regex |\n    29→| HIGH | 8-2 | `getDefaultState()` hardcoded `coverage.tool` to `'c8'` regardless of stack — Rust projects got wrong default | Yes |\n    30→| MEDIUM | 8-1 | `[[bin]]` and `[lib]` matched inside TOML comments | Yes — used line-anchored regexes |\n    31→| MEDIUM | 8-1 | Missing test coverage for 3 of 5 web frameworks (rocket, tide, warp) | Yes — tests added |\n    32→| MEDIUM | 8-1 | Missing test for `[lib]` + `[[bin]]` dual-crate pattern | Yes |\n    33→| MEDIUM | 8-2 | `detectCoverageTool()` had no rust branch — Cargo.toml projects fell to `'unknown'` | Yes |\n    34→| MEDIUM | 8-2 | `getStackLabel('rust')` returned `'Unknown'` — AGENTS.md mislabeled Rust projects | Yes |\n    35→| MEDIUM | 8-2 | `generateAgentsMdContent()` had no rust branch — Rust projects got \"No recognized stack\" boilerplate | Yes |\n    36→| LOW | 8-1 | `getCargoDepsSection()` does not handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline subsection TOML style | No — accepted per NFR4 |\n    37→| LOW | 8-2 | Duplicate stack-to-tool mapping in `getCoverageTool()` (docs-scaffold.ts) and `getDefaultCoverageTool()` (state.ts) | No — tracked as tech debt |\n    38→\n    39→### Workarounds / Tech Debt Introduced\n    40→\n    41→- **Cargo.toml parsing uses string matching, not a proper TOML parser.** Deliberate per NFR4 (no new deps), but `[dependencies.foo]` subsections and comments containing dep names are edge cases that remain unhandled.\n    42→- **Library crates map to `generic` AppType** rather than a dedicated `'library'` type. Libraries are indistinguishable from unknown projects.\n    43→- **`coverage.tool` type was tightened** from plain `string` to a union type. Non-breaking but undocumented migration — existing state files with unexpected string values would still typecheck at runtime.\n    44→\n    45→### Verification Gaps\n    46→\n    47→- **8-2 AC2 initially failed.** The `rust_env_hint` field was missing from OTLP state for Rust projects. Required a separate fix commit (`9ddd65e`) before the verification commit (`d6a76bf`).\n    48→- **State snapshot still shows 8-2 as `verifying`**, while sprint-status.yaml shows `done`. Sync drift.\n    49→- **~40 pre-existing TypeScript compilation errors** in test files (bridge.test.ts, run.test.ts, etc.). Tests pass at runtime via Vitest despite `tsc --noEmit` errors. These are unrelated to this session but create noise during verification.\n    50→- **`parseCoverageReport` has no `'tarpaulin-json'` parser** — out of scope for 8-2, deferred to story 8-3.\n    51→\n    52→### Tooling / Infrastructure Problems\n    53→\n    54→- **Leftover container:** Previous session left `codeharness-verify` container running. Had to clean up before starting fresh verification.\n    55→- **Stack detection mismatch:** `codeharness status --check-docker` reported stack as down, but shared stack containers were running under `codeharness-shared-*` naming. `docker-compose.harness.yml` tried to start duplicate containers and hit port conflicts.\n    56→- **Observability gap:** Both AC1 and AC2 verifications showed no log events emitted to VictoriaLogs during `codeharness init` operations. Silent code path — the init command does not emit structured telemetry.\n    57→- **Beads sync failure:** `codeharness sync` couldn't find the story Status line in the story file — likely a pattern mismatch (`## Status:` format).\n    58→- **Ralph timeout:** Iteration 1 timed out at 30 minutes. The agent was writing a retrospective file when it was killed. Useful work was lost (the retro had to be regenerated).\n    59→\n    60→---\n    61→\n    62→## 3. What Went Well\n    63→\n    64→- **Two stories completed in a single session** (~38 minutes wall clock). Both stories in Epic 8.1 (Rust Detection Foundation) are done.\n    65→- **Thorough bug-finding during review.** The implementation subagent found and fixed 10 issues across both stories before verification, including two HIGH-severity false-positive bugs in Cargo.toml parsing.\n    66→- **Good test coverage.** Story 8-1 achieved 97.02% overall coverage with all 123 files above 80% floor. Multiple missing test scenarios were identified and added (web framework variants, dual-crate pattern).\n    67→- **Clean commits.** Three commits, each with clear scope: feature, fix, verification.\n    68→- **Existing test adjusted correctly.** The test using `'rust'` as an \"unrecognized stack\" was updated to `'java'` now that Rust is recognized.\n    69→\n    70→---\n    71→\n    72→## 4. What Went Wrong\n    73→\n    74→- **Ralph iteration 1 timed out.** 30 minutes was not enough for impl+verify of two stories plus retrospective writing. The timeout killed the agent mid-write.\n    75→- **8-2 AC2 failed first verification pass.** The `rust_env_hint` field in OTLP state was missed during initial implementation. Required a fix commit and re-verify cycle.\n    76→- **Docker naming inconsistency** between shared stack (`codeharness-shared-*`) and the compose file's expected container names caused port conflicts and wasted verification time.\n    77→- **Beads sync is still broken.** The `codeharness sync` command fails to find story status headers, a problem carried forward from previous epics. Story file statuses remain stuck at `ready-for-dev`.\n    78→- **State snapshot desync.** `state-snapshot.json` shows 8-2 as `verifying` while `sprint-status.yaml` shows `done`. No mechanism ensures these stay consistent.\n    79→\n    80→---\n    81→\n    82→## 5. Lessons Learned\n    83→\n    84→### Repeat\n    85→- **Review-then-fix before verification** caught 10 bugs. The pattern of having the agent review its own implementation for edge cases before running verification pays off consistently.\n    86→- **Separate fix commits from feature commits.** The `9ddd65e` fix commit for 8-2 AC2 kept the git history clean and traceable.\n    87→\n    88→### Avoid\n    89→- **Don't rely on `codeharness sync`** for story status updates — it's been broken for 9+ epics. Update story files manually or fix the sync command.\n    90→- **Don't assume Docker container naming is consistent.** The shared stack uses different container names than what the status check expects. This causes false \"stack down\" reports and port conflicts.\n    91→- **Don't schedule retrospective writing within the same timeout window as impl+verify.** The retro was killed mid-write on iteration 1 because it started too late in the 30-minute window.\n    92→\n    93→---\n    94→\n    95→## 6. Action Items\n    96→\n    97→### Fix Now (before next session)\n    98→- [ ] Reconcile `state-snapshot.json` — set 8-2 status to `done` to match `sprint-status.yaml`\n    99→- [ ] Clean up any leftover Docker containers from this session (`codeharness-verify`, duplicates)\n   100→\n   101→### Fix Soon (next sprint)\n   102→- [ ] Fix Docker container naming: align `codeharness status --check-docker` detection with `codeharness-shared-*` naming convention, or vice versa\n   103→- [ ] Add `rust_env_hint` field to init-time telemetry so VictoriaLogs captures Rust project setup events (observability gap)\n   104→- [ ] Extract duplicate `stack -> coverage_tool` mapping into a single utility function (duplicated in docs-scaffold.ts and state.ts)\n   105→- [ ] Add `'library'` AppType for Rust `[lib]`-only crates instead of mapping them to `generic`\n   106→\n   107→### Backlog (track but not urgent)\n   108→- [ ] Fix `codeharness sync` story status header pattern matching (carried 9+ epics)\n   109→- [ ] Fix ~40 pre-existing TypeScript compilation errors in test files\n   110→- [ ] Handle `[dependencies.foo]` inline TOML subsection style in `getCargoDepsSection()`\n   111→- [ ] Write integration test for `detectStack` -> `detectAppType` end-to-end flow\n   112→- [ ] Implement `tarpaulin-json` parser in `parseCoverageReport` (story 8-3 scope)\n   113→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_012rEfMEVTSN67tDuqBLhH5b","session_id":"900ad046-8ed4-4678-b2b2-9fd66fbde286","uuid":"b110e8ca-0d5f-4272-b196-6da339274cba","timestamp":"2026-03-23T06:08:30.023Z"}
